<p><strong>Consider the following Autodesk products:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/autocad">AutoCAD</a>, <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/autocad-architecture">AutoCAD Architecture</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/revit">Revit</a>, <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/dynamo-studio">Dynamo Studio</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/3ds-max">3DS Max</a>, <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/maya">Maya</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/sketchbook-students">Sketchbook</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/products/fusion-360/students-teachers-educators">Fusion 360</a></li>
</ul>

<hr />

<p><strong>Standard Tips</strong>
<img src="../img/software/tips.png" alt="alt text" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Advanced web collaboration tools for detail-driven project management.</li>
  <li>Can also mark up 3D models, but so much can be done with PDF and images.</li>
  <li>Great tool for handling mixed media in a single project repository.</li>
  <li>Has advanced rendering and texture mapping capabilities.</li>
  <li>Free via CMU, <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/free-software/featured">most AutoDesk products are free for students.</a></li>
</ul>
